article.description: Justin Roberts registered 13 points and six assists as Georgia State topped Mercer 73-61 on Saturday.
article.headline: Roberts scores 13 to lift Georgia State past Mercer 73-61
article.linkText: Roberts scores 13 to lift Georgia State past Mercer 73-61
article.story: MACON, Ga. -- Justin Roberts registered 13 points and six assists as Georgia State topped Mercer 73-61 on Saturday. Corey Allen had 16 points for Georgia State (6-3), which won its fifth straight game. Damon Wilson added 16 points and Kane Williams had 12. Mercer put up 18 points in the first half, a season low for the team. Victor Bafutto had 14 points for the Bears (4-6), who have now lost four games in a row. Djordje Dimitrijevic added 14 points. Ethan Stair had 13 points and eight rebounds. Georgia State plays Texas-Arlington at home next Thursday. Mercer matches up against UNC Wilmington on the road next Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
